      • toString

        public String toString(int format)
        Description copied from interface: IFIXMessage
        Returns a string representation of the message.

        The string is formatted according to the value of format as follows:

        • IFIXMessage.FORMAT_SUMMARY - Summary format.
        • IFIXMessage.FORMAT_SUMMARY_VERBOSE - Summary format but with more details.
        • IFIXMessage.FORMAT_FULL - Full format.
        • IFIXMessage.FORMAT_VERBOSE - Full format with tag names instead of values.
        • IFIXMessage.FORMAT_RAW_IN - Raw input data from which message was constructed.
        • any other value - Summary format.
        Specified by:
        toString in interface IFIXMessage
        Overrides:
        toString in class FIXMessageDecoratorBase
        Parameters:
        format - Required format of returned String - should take one of the above values.
        Returns:
        String representation of message.

      • iterator

        public ListIterator<ITagValue> iterator()
        Description copied from interface: ITagValueIterableFromTag
        Create an iterator over a collection of ITagValues.

        The following methods are not supported by the returned iterator:

        • java.util.ListIterator#remove()
        • java.util.ListIterator#add()
        • java.util.ListIterator#set()

        Calling any of them results in an UnsupportedOperationException.

        This method guarantees that a new iterator instance is returned with each call.

        The ITagValue objects returned are references to the underlying data, however, there are no guarantees regarding whether objects are created or not. Changing the values of these objects changes the underlying data. To avoid this behaviour you can use ITagValue.copyFrom(ITagValue) to copy the returned value before modifying it. If you intend on storing the returned ITagValue then copying it first is highly recommended.

        Specified by:
        iterator in interface ITagValueIterableFromTag<ListIterator<ITagValue>>
        Specified by:
        iterator in interface Iterable<ITagValue>
        Overrides:
        iterator in class FIXMessageDecoratorBase
        Returns:
        Iterator over ITagValues. Guaranteed to be a new instance for each call.
